<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/178: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-06T13:00:00-03:00"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1921—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>12. Department’s February 4, 1 p.m. Brazilian Government will recognize
                            the new Bolivian Government conjointly on February 9.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>